channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: LA City Council Removes U-Turn Traffic Signs Because They Say They're Anti-Gay - We Can't Have Anything
Rule of law on ballot in NYC suburbs as cop, veteran trade barbs over border crisis, policing
item.description: Rep. Pat Ryan, D-N.Y., and Republican challenger Alison Esposito, who ran as Lee Zeldin's gubernatorial running mate in 2022, sounded off on their key swing district race.

item.title: DOJ Won't Prosecute Garland for Contempt, Says Refusal to Provide Audio Not a Crime
item.description: Attorney General Merrick Garland will not be prosecuted for contempt of Congress because his refusal to turn over audio of President Joe Biden's interview in his classified documents case "did not constitute a crime," the Justice Department said Friday.In a letter to House...

item.title: Remembering the Man Who Made Me a Conservative
DOJ won't prosecute AG Garland for contempt for refusal to turn over audio from Biden, Hur interview
item.description: The Justice Department will not prosecute U.S. Attorney General Merrick Garland over contempt after House Republicans voted Wednesday to hold him in contempt.

item.title: Biden Slams Supreme Court Bump Stock Decision
item.description: President Joe Biden denounced the Supreme Court's decision on Friday to overturn a federal ban on bump stocks and called on Congress to take action.

item.title: More Disturbing Reports From G7 About Biden 'Losing Focus'
House Democratic leader declares Justice Alito 'an insurrectionist sympathizer' amid flag fracas
item.description: House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries, D-N.Y., slammed Supreme Court Justice Samuel Alito as an insurrectionist amid an unfolding saga over the flying of a flag at his home.

item.title: Sabatini Drops Out of House Race After Trump Endorses Opponent
item.description: Former Florida Republican legislator Anthony Sabatini on Thursday dropped out of the GOP primary for his congressional race, hours after Donald Trump endorsed his opponent, incumbent U.S. Rep. Daniel Webster.

item.title: Everything's Bigger: 75,000 Square Foot Buc-ee's Opens in Texas
Lawmakers push Biden admin to pay more attention to northern border threats
item.description: More than a dozen House Republicans are pushing for more resources and analysis of the northern border as the U.S. continues to grapple with a migrant crisis.

item.title: Rep. Steil to Newsmax: Biden Admin Forcing Agencies to Drive Partisan Agenda
item.description: Rep. Bryan Steil, R-Wis., told Newsmax he wants to investigate what administrative agencies are doing to advance President Joe Biden's partisan agenda.

item.title: Putin Delivers Ultimatum to Ukraine and the West
Trump's campaign says Supreme Court’s decision striking down his admin's bump stock rule ‘should be respected'
item.description: The campaign for former President Donald Trump said the Supreme Court's decision to strike down a Trump-era ban on bump stocks should be 'respected.'

item.title: Trump: AI Rewrote Speech 'So Beautifully'
